            42 => [
                'id' => 44,
                'title' => 'An Orthodox Catechism - Lord\'s Day 2: Sin and Misery (Questions 2-3)',
                'type' => 'catechism',
                'text' => '<h3>Leader</h3><p>How many things are necessary for you to know that you, enjoying this comfort, may live and die happily?</p><h3>Congregation</h3><p>Three. The first: what is the greatness of my sin and misery. The second: how am I delivered from all sin and misery. The third: what thanks I owe to God for this delivery.</p><h3>Leader</h3><p>From where do you know your misery?</p><h3>Congregation</h3><p>Out of the Law of God.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-02 19:51:49',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-02 19:51:49',
            ],
            43 => [
                'id' => 45,
                'title' => 'Be Thou My Vision (Day 6)',
                'type' => 'prayer',
                'text' => '<p>O Lord God, Father of mercies, the fountain of comfort and blessing, of life and peace, of plenty and pardon, who fills heaven with your glory, and earth with your goodness—We give you the most earnest, the most humble, and most enlarged returns of our glad and thankful hearts, for you have refreshed us with your comforts, and enlarged us with your blessing. You have made our flesh and bones to rejoice, for, besides the blessings of all mankind, the blessings of nature, and the blessings of grace, the support of every minute, and the comforts of every day, you have opened your bosom, and at this time have poured out an excellent expression of your loving kindness.</p><p>Grant, Almighty God, that as you shine on us by your Word, we may not be blind at midday, nor willfully seek darkness, and thus lull our minds asleep; but may we be roused daily by your words, and may we stir up ourselves more and more to fear your name and thus present ourselves and all our pursuits as a sacrifice to you, that you may peaceably rule, and perpetually dwell in us, until you gather us to your celestial habitation, where there is reserved for us eternal rest and glory, through Jesus Christ our Lord. Amen.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-02 19:57:22',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-02 19:57:22',
            ],
            44 => [
                'id' => 46,
                'title' => 'Exodus 20:1-17',
                'type' => 'law',
                'text' => '<h3>Leader</h3><p>And God spoke all these words, saying, “I am the LORD your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery. You shall have no other gods before me. You shall not make for yourself a carved image, or any likeness of anything that is in heaven above, or that is in the earth beneath, or that is in the water under the earth. You shall not bow down to them or serve them, for I the LORD your God am a jealous God, visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children to the third and the fourth generation of those who hate me, but showing steadfast love to thousands of those who love me and keep my commandments. You shall not take the name of the LORD your God in vain. Remember the Sabbath day, to keep it holy. Six days you shall labor, and do all your work, but the seventh day is a Sabbath to the LORD your God. Honor your father and your mother, that your days may be long in the land that the LORD your God is giving you. You shall not murder. You shall not commit adultery. You shall not steal. You shall not bear false witness against your neighbor. You shall not covet your neighbor’s house; you shall not covet your neighbor’s wife, or his male servant, or his female servant, or his ox, or his donkey, or anything that is your neighbor’s.”</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-09 17:46:26',
