            52 => [
                'id' => 54,
                'title' => 'Hebrews 13:20-21',
                'type' => 'benediction',
                'text' => '<h3>Leader</h3><p>Now may the God of peace who brought again from the dead our Lord Jesus, the great shepherd of the sheep, by the blood of the eternal covenant, equip you with everything good that you may do his will, working in us that which is pleasing in his sight, through Jesus Christ, to whom be glory forever and ever. Amen.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-15 23:10:26',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-15 23:10:26',
            ],
            53 => [
                'id' => 55,
                'title' => 'Psalm 39:7-8, 12 - O Lord, for what do I wait',
                'type' => 'confession-of-sin',
                'text' => '<h3>Congregation</h3><p>And now, O Lord, for what do I wait? My hope is in you. Deliver me from all my transgressions. Do not make me the scorn of the fool! Hear my prayer, O LORD, and give ear to my cry; hold not your peace at my tears! For I am a sojourner with you, a guest, like all my fathers.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-15 23:12:39',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-15 23:12:39',
            ],
            54 => [
                'id' => 56,
                'title' => 'Zechariah 12:10, 13:1, 9',
                'type' => 'assurance-of-pardon',
                'text' => '<h3>Leader</h3><p>And I will pour out on the house of David and the inhabitants of Jerusalem a spirit of grace and pleas for mercy, so that, when they look on me, on him whom they have pierced, they shall mourn for him, as one mourns for an only child, and weep bitterly over him, as one weeps over a firstborn. On that day there shall be a fountain opened for the house of David and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, to cleanse them from sin and uncleanness. They will call upon my name, and I will answer them. I will say, ‘They are my people’; and they will say, ‘The LORD is my God.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-15 23:13:44',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-15 23:13:44',
            ],
            55 => [
                'id' => 57,
                'title' => 'An Orthodox Catechism - Lord\'s Day 4: Creation and Corruption (Questions 6-8)',
                'type' => 'catechism',
                'text' => '<h3>Leader</h3><p>Did God then make man so wicked and perverse?</p><h3>Congregation</h3><p>Not so, but rather he made man good, and in his own image; that is, endowed with true righteousness and holiness, that man might rightly know God, his Creator, and heartily love him, and live with him blessed forever, and that to praise and magnify him.</p><h3>Leader</h3><p>From where then arises this wickedness of man’s nature?</p><h3>Congregation</h3><p>From the fall and disobedience of our first parents, Adam and Eve, hence is our nature so corrupt that we are all conceived and born in sin.</p><h3>Leader</h3><p>Are we so corrupt that we are not at all apt to do well, but are prone to all vice?</p><h3>Congregation</h3><p>Indeed, we are, except we be regenerated by the Holy Spirit.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-15 23:24:10',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-15 23:24:10',
            ],
            56 => [
                'id' => 58,
                'title' => 'Be Thou My Vision (Day 11)',
                'type' => 'prayer',
                'text' => '<h3>Leader</h3><p>Almighty God, Father of all mercies, as your unworthy servants, we give you most humble and heartfelt thanks for all your goodness and loving-kindness to us and to all people. We bless you for our creation, preservation, and all the blessings of this life, but above all, for your precious love in the redemption of the world by our Lord Jesus Christ, for the means of grace, and for the hope of glory. And we pray that you would give us that due sense of all your mercies that our hearts may be sincerely thankful and that we may show forth your praise not only with our lips but in our lives, by giving up ourselves to your service and by walking before you in holiness and righteousness all our days, through Jesus Christ our Lord, to whom with you and the Holy Spirit, be all honor and glory world without end.</p><p>We pray, O God, pour out upon us your Holy Spirit—the Spirit of prayer—that we may ever love and desire to pray; being daily free to approach you, with all confidence in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ; to bow before you in every time of need, as children well beloved, O most beloved Father, you who are really a Father unto all your children in heaven and on earth.</p><p>Grant that we may always lift up unto you holy hands, without fear or doubt, and in full assurance that all our prayers and sighs which come from the heart, are truly heard. Grant also that when our help delays we shall be patient, not dictating to you either time or measure, but to wait and abide your own good time; for you have pleasure in them that fear and put their trust in your mercy.</p><p>Divine Spirit, illumine to us the words of the Lord. Show us the wealth of glory that lies beneath the old familiar stories. Teach us the depths of meaning hidden in the songs of Zion. Raise us to the heights of aspiration that is reached by the wings of the prophet. Lift us to the summit of faith that is trod by the feet of the apostle. Open our eyes, that we may behold wondrous things out of your law. Amen.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-15 23:41:36',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-15 23:41:36',
            ],
            57 => [
                'id' => 59,
                'title' => 'Romans 9:25-26',
                'type' => 'call-to-worship',
                'text' => '<h3>Leader</h3><p>As it also says in Hosea, I will call Not My People, My People, and she who is Unloved, Beloved. And it will be in the place where they were told, you are not my people, there they will be called sons of the living God.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-23 13:28:50',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-23 13:28:50',
            ],
            58 => [
                'id' => 60,
                'title' => 'A Dying Savior\'s Love',
                'type' => 'benediction',
                'text' => '<h3>Leader</h3><p>Now a dying Saviour’s love, a risen Saviour’s joy, an ascended Saviour’s power, and a returning Saviour’s hope, rest upon your hearts and homes.</p><h3>Congregation</h3><p>Amen.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-23 13:29:45',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-23 13:29:45',
            ],
            59 => [
                'id' => 61,
                'title' => 'Deuteronomy 10:12-16',
                'type' => 'law',
                'text' => '<h3>Leader</h3><p>And now, Israel, what does the LORD your God require of you, but to fear the LORD your God, to walk in all his ways, to love him, to serve the LORD your God with all your heart and with all your soul, and to keep the commandments and statutes of the LORD, which I am commanding you today for your good? Behold, to the LORD your God belong heaven and the heaven of heavens, the earth with all that is in it. Yet the LORD set his heart in love on your fathers and chose their offspring after them, you above all peoples, as you are this day. Circumcise therefore the foreskin of your heart, and be no longer stubborn.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-23 13:30:36',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-23 13:30:36',
            ],
            60 => [
                'id' => 62,
                'title' => 'Psalm 51:1-4 - Have Mercy on Me, O God',
                'type' => 'confession-of-sin',
                'text' => '<h3>Congregation</h3><p>Have mercy on me, O God, according to your steadfast love; according to your abundant mercy blot out my transgressions. Wash me thoroughly from my iniquity, and cleanse me from my sin! For I know my transgressions, and my sin is ever before me. Against you, you only, have I sinned and done what is evil in your sight, so that you may be justified in your words and blameless in your judgment.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-23 13:33:26',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-23 13:33:26',
            ],
            61 => [
                'id' => 63,
                'title' => 'An Orthodox Catechism - Lord\'s Day 5: God\'s Justice and Mercy (Questions 9-11)',
                'type' => 'catechism',
                'text' => '<h3>Leader</h3><p>Does not God then do injustice to man, who in the law requires that of him which he is not able to perform?</p><h3>Congregation</h3><p>No, for God had made man such as he might perform it, but man, by the impulsion of the devil, and his own stubbornness, bereaved himself and all his posterity of those divine graces.</p><h3>Leader</h3><p>Does God leave this stubbornness and falling away of man unpunished?</p><h3>Congregation</h3><p>No, but is angry in a most dreadful manner, as well for the sin in which we are born, as also for those which we ourselves commit, and in most just judgement punishes them with present and everlasting punishments, as he himself pronounces, “Everyone who does not do everything written in the book of the law is cursed.”</p><h3>Leader</h3><p>Is not God then merciful?</p><h3>Congregation</h3><p>Yes, truly he is merciful, but in so, he is also just, because his justice requires that the sin committed against the divine majesty of God should also be repaid with extreme, that is, everlasting punishment, both in body and soul.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-23 16:24:14',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-23 16:24:14',
            ],
            62 => [
                'id' => 64,
                'title' => 'Lord God, The Great and Only King',
                'type' => 'prayer',
                'text' => '<p>Lord God, The Great And Only King, you have made summer and winter, day and night; each of these revolutions serves our welfare and is full of your care and kindness.</p><p>Your bounty is seen in the relations that train us, the laws that defend us, the homes that shelter us, the food that builds us, the garments that comfort us, the continuance of our health, members, senses, understanding, memory, affection, will.</p><p>But as stars fade before the rising sun, you have eclipsed all these benefits in the wisdom and grace that purposed redemption by Jesus your Son. Blessed be your mercy that laid help on one that is mighty and willing, one that is able to save to the uttermost.</p><p>Make us deeply sensible of our need of his saving grace, of the blood that cleanses, of the rest he has promised. And impute to us that righteousness which justifies the guilty, gives them a title to eternal life, and possession of the Spirit. May we love the freeness of salvation, and joy in its holiness;</p><p>Grow our understanding of your word and your great works that we know you; Give us faith to grasp your promises, that are our hope, provide for every exigency, and prevent every evil; Keep our hearts from straying after forbidden pleasures; May your will bind all our wishes; Let us live out of the world as to its spirit, maxim, manners, but live in it as the sphere of our action and usefulness; May we be alive to every call of duty, accepting without question your determination of our circumstances and our service. Amen.</p>',
                'created_at' => '2025-08-23 16:28:17',
                'updated_at' => '2025-08-23 16:28:17',
            ],
        ]);

    }
